div.span: Recognition performance e.g., accuracy, hit/false alarm rates
Source memory performance AI vs. Human attribution

Read two collaborator descriptions both target characters are educators:
AI collaborator: typically relies on AI to complete tasks
Human collaborator: typically works with colleagues

Each adjective paired with AI or Human collaborator
balanced, randomized

Suitability judgment for each adjective:
F = suitable; J = not suitable

Distractor task 5 minutes:
Mental arithmetic addition and subtraction
Participants are unaware of the upcoming memory test until distractor completes

120 adjectives in random order
80 old from study, 40 new

Old/New recognition judgment
F = old; J = new

If old: source judgment
Was it paired with AI or Human?
Key assignment counterbalanced across participants
If new: proceed to next trial
Chinese Adjective Lexicon for Fundamental Dimensions of Social Cognition Han et al., 2015

120 adjectives total; 4 categories x 30 each
Positive Warmth, Negative Warmth, Positive Competence, Negative Competence

Per participant: 20 per category used in study 80 total
Remaining 10 per category serve as new in test 40 total

Randomization and balancing:
Adjective-to-collaborator pairing balanced
Trial order randomized
Social cognition dimension: Warmth vs. Competence
Dependent variables: memory performance recognition, source; guessing parameters in source-monitoring
